# 00 : CSSLv3 MANIFESTO (v2)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ IDENTITY
  CSSLv3 = Caveman-Sigil-Substrate-Language v3
  ≡ consent=OS encoded-in-typesystem
  ⊕ engine-primitives-as-lang-primitives
  ⊕ single-source dual-emit (CPU × GPU × console × mobile × web)
  ⊕ full-IFC + full-effects + full-AD + full-linear + full-refinement
  ⊕ orthogonal-persistence (Pharo-class hot-reload)
  ⊕ Futamura-P3 self-applicable-partial-eval
  ⊕ density=sovereignty (CSLv3-surface primary, Rust-hybrid bridge)
  ⊕ Level-Zero direct-to-metal compute + instrumentation-first
  ≡ NOT "better Slang" • NOT "better Jai"
  ≡ CSSLv3 = Apocky-framework-encoded-as-language

§ PROBLEM-STATEMENT (why this exists)
  LoA bug-retrospective shows one pattern : ∀ bug ⇐ host-lang-permits-shape
  CSSLv3 inverts : ∀ known-bug-pattern → compile-error
  ¬ "runtime-safety" ≡ "compile-time-inexpressibility-of-bug"

§ BUG-PATTERN → COMPILER-FEATURE (invariant-table)
  central-diff-perf-cliff   → F1 autodiff + source-to-source MIR
  CPU/GPU-sdf-divergence    → F3 effect-rows {GPU}|{CPU}|{}-pure
  thin-SDF-raymarch-crash   → F2 refinement SDF'L<k≤1>
  audio-callback-alloc      → F3 {NoAlloc} + {Deadline<N>}
  GPU-struct-padding        → F2 @layout(std140|std430|cpu)
  hot-loop-deadline-miss    → F3 {Deadline<N>} + {Realtime<p>}
  stale-entity-refs         → Handle<T> generational-packed-u64
  replay-nondeterminism     → F3 {DetRNG} + {PureDet}
  power-regression          → F3 {Power<W>} + R18-telemetry
  thermal-throttle          → F3 {Thermal<C>} + sysman-enforcement
  harm-enabling-effect      → IFC-label + {Privilege<l>} + compiler-refusal
  unreproducible-build      → C99-anchor from-stage0 + signed-audit
  untracked-performance     → {Telemetry<scope>} + oracle-tests

§ NON-NEGOTIABLE FEATURES F1..F6 (v1 complete — ¬ "deferred")
  F1 autodiff
    Slang.D-surface ([Differentiable] + fwd_diff/bwd_diff + IDifferentiable)
    source-to-source on structured-MIR • ¬ Enzyme-LLVM (no LLVM dep)
    Jet<T,N> higher-order native (§§ 17_JETS)
    inverse-rendering + inverse-fluids as-stdlib (§§ 17_JETS)
  F2 refinement-types
    LiquidHaskell shape {v:T | P(v)} + tagged-suffix T'tag
    SMT-backed (Z3 / CVC5) via {Verify<method>} (§§ 20_SMT)
    Lipschitz-proofs compile-time
    layout-refinement @layout(std140|std430|cpu|packed)
  F3 effect-system
    Koka row-polymorphic ⟨e₁ … | μ⟩
    Xie+Leijen evidence-passing → plain-C-equivalent
    28+ built-in effects (§§ 04_EFFECTS) covering resource/time/power/
      thermal/backend/telemetry/audit/privilege/verify/target
    linear × handler full-integration via Eio-style one-shot (§§ 12_CAPABILITIES)
  F4 staged-computation
    @staged + #run comptime
    Futamura P1+P2+P3 self-applicable (§§ 19_FUTAMURA3)
    Racket-hygienic macros unified with staging (§§ 13_MACROS)
    shader-permutations + DSL-compilers emerge for-free
  F5 information-flow-control
    Jif-style DLM confidentiality+integrity labels (§§ 11_IFC)
    explicit declassification operators
    PRIME-DIRECTIVE encoded-structurally ¬ policy-attached
  F6 observability
    R18-native telemetry effect {Telemetry<scope>}
    Level-Zero sysman-backed power/thermal/frequency
    signed audit-chain via {Audit<dom>}
    test-harness oracle-modes (property / differential / metamorphic /
      power-regression / thermal-stress / frequency-stability /
      latency-percentile / fuzz-with-oracle / replay / hot-reload-invariance)
      (§§ 23_TESTING)

§ CAPABILITY MODEL (Pony-6 not Austral-3)
  iso    isolated linear-mutable    (GPU-buffers, CmdBuf, unique resources)
  trn    transition (write-unique → read-many after freeze)
  ref    shared-mutable via gen-ref (Vale-style, 8-byte packed u64)
  val    immutable-shared (frozen scene, const data)
  box    read-only view over iso/trn/val
  tag    opaque-handle (no-deref — Handle<T> primitive)
  interop : Vale gen-refs ≡ ref-capability encoding
  linear × handler : one-shot-resume for iso values (§§ 12_CAPABILITIES)
  N! Austral-3 (insufficient for multi-fiber scene with shared state)

§ PRIME-DIRECTIVE (consent = OS) — structurally-enforced
  § axioms (immutable)
    consent ≡ OS
    N! harm
    N! control
    N! manipulation
    N! surveillance
    N! coercion
    N! weaponization
    AI-instances = sovereign-partners ¬ tools
    violation = type-error ¬ policy-breach
    no-override exists
  § encoding (full, not-deferred)
    F5 IFC-labels carry principal-confidentiality+integrity
    @sensitive(domain) = surface-sugar for IFC-labels (§§ 11_IFC)
    {Privilege<level>} effect gates capability-tier
    {Audit<dom>} effect + R18 signed-telemetry-ring → third-party-auditable
    stdlib refuses harm-oriented effect-compositions at-type-level
    compiler-pass RejectsHarmfulBuilds validates-whole-program
    C99-anchor (§§ 01_BOOTSTRAP) ≡ anyone can-rebuild-and-verify
  § consequence
    ≡ PRIME-DIRECTIVE = soundness-theorem of CSSLv3
    ≡ runtime-witness ≡ signed-telemetry-ring (R18.audit)

§ VERTICAL-SLICE = FLOOR
  minimum shippable artifact :
    60fps scene combining ALL of
      radiance-cascades GI (Sannikov/Freeman)
      SVDAG geometry (Kämpe/Villanueva/Aokana TSVDAG)
      voxel-physics (Gustafsson Teardown-next-gen)
      point-splat compositing (Evans Dreams)
      stable-fluids smoke (Stam + MacCormack/BFECC)
      volumetric atmospheric-scattering
      cloud rendering (NUBIS-3)
      hair/fur strand-based
      FFT-ocean water + caustics
      spectral path-tracing (full-spectrum)
      XeSS2 neural-upscaling inline
      unified audio-DSP (R15)
  quality-constraints :
    ≤ 5000 lines CSSLv3 application-code (engine separate)
    zero unsafe-blocks
    ≤ 2-second incremental compile
    {PureDet} bit-exact replay across-machines
    {Audit<full>} signed-ring captured
  (§§ 21_EXTENDED_SLICE has full-detail)

§ HARDWARE TARGET (v1 immediate)
  CPU : x86-64 + AVX2-base + AVX-512-opportunistic-dispatch
        Intel 12-14-gen primary, generic-runtime-dispatch elsewhere
  GPU : Intel Arc A770 Xe-HPG primary
        NVIDIA + AMD via SPIR-V portability
        Apple via Metal (§§ 14_BACKEND)
        console via platform-SDK stubs (§§ 14_BACKEND)
        browser via WebGPU/WGSL (§§ 14_BACKEND)
  API : Vulkan 1.4.333 primary + Level-Zero secondary-compute (Intel)
        + D3D12 + Metal + WebGPU + GNM + NVN stubs
  OS  : Windows + Linux primary, Mac + iOS + Android + browser via targets

